<p>Rajya Sabha MP Raghav Chadha has found himself at the center of a major political controversy after the Punjab government reportedly withdrew his Z+ category security cover. The move comes at a time when tensions between Chadha and the Aam Aadmi Party leadership appear to be growing stronger.</p>

<p>Raghav Chadha, one of the most recognizable leaders of the AAP, was earlier given Z+ security by the Punjab Police because of his position and public profile. However, reports now suggest that the Punjab government quietly removed the security cover last week.</p>

<p>The decision has triggered political debate because Chadha has recently been facing criticism from within his own party. He was removed from the post of deputy leader in the Rajya Sabha, which many political observers saw as a sign that his relationship with senior AAP leaders had become strained.</p>

